<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
      Developer-ID DMG variant of Splynek's entitlements.  Distinct
      from Resources/Splynek-MAS.entitlements which is what the App
      Store build signs against.

      v2.0.1 release-blocker fix (2026-05-13):
        The previous version of this file included iCloud entitlements
        (com.apple.developer.icloud-services + container-identifiers)
        alongside `com.apple.security.app-sandbox = true`.  That
        combination is invalid for a Developer-ID build: a sandboxed
        app that accesses an iCloud container needs an
        `application-identifier` entitlement, which only ships inside
        a provisioning profile — and Developer-ID signing has no
        profile.  Launchd refused to spawn the resulting binary with
        `RBSRequestErrorDomain Code=5 / POSIX 163` ("Launchd job spawn
        failed") on every fresh user machine.  Notarisation passed
        because signatures + executable validity check OK, but
        runtime sandbox init failed.

        Fix: drop iCloud from the DMG variant.  CloudKit over-cellular
        relay (the only consumer) was already gated behind `#if MAS_BUILD`
        in FleetCoordinator.swift + TrustWatchCloudKitNotifier.swift
        (commit 276d6ec, 2026-05-10), so the DMG variant doesn't try
        to use those entitlements at runtime anyway.  iPhone Companion
        users who need over-cellular relay use the MAS variant.

      Sandbox stays enabled for the DMG variant — it's a good security
      posture for a download manager and notarisation expects it for
      apps that ship with hardened runtime.  Splynek's needs:
        - Outgoing network access (client) for HTTP downloads
        - Incoming network access (server) for the LAN HTTP API + Bonjour
        - Write access to ~/Downloads
        - Write access to user-picked locations (NSOpenPanel)

      To build the DMG variant with this entitlements file:
        SIGN_IDENTITY="Developer ID Application: …" \
          ENTITLEMENTS=Resources/Splynek.entitlements \
          ./Scripts/build.sh
    -->
    <key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.network.server</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.files.user-selected.read-write</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.files.downloads.read-write</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
